---
import ArticleLayout from '../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';

const locale = 'en';
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How WorthCalc handles your data: all calculators run client-side, plus details on Google AdSense and analytics cookies."
  locale={locale}
  updated="2026-07-03"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains what happens to your information when you use
    WorthCalc. The short version: every calculator runs inside your own
    browser, we do not collect the numbers you type in, and this page tells
    you exactly what third-party services (like advertising) might still set
    cookies on your device.
  </p>

  <h2>Calculator data</h2>
  <p>
    All calculators on WorthCalc — installment APR, subscription audit, Costco
    membership, EV vs. gas, rent vs. buy, commute cost, latte factor, and
    cashback break-even — run entirely as JavaScript in your browser. There is
    no custom backend server that receives the prices, income figures, loan
    terms, or any other numbers you enter. Nothing you type into a calculator
    is transmitted to us. Some calculators may save your inputs in your
    browser's localStorage purely so your numbers are still there if you
    reload the page; that data stays on your device and is never uploaded. You
    can clear it at any time from the tool itself or from your browser's site
    data settings.
  </p>

  <h2>Google AdSense and third-party advertising cookies</h2>
  <p>
    WorthCalc is supported by advertising, including Google AdSense. Google
    and its advertising partners may use cookies, device identifiers, and
    similar technologies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this or
    other websites, and to measure ad performance. This is sometimes called
    "personalized" or "interest-based" advertising.
  </p>
  <p>
    Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on a
    user's prior visits to this website or other websites. Google's use of
    advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to you based
    on your visit to this site and/or other sites on the Internet. You may opt
    out of personalized advertising by visiting Google's Ads Settings at
    <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.google.com/settings/ads</a>.
    You can also learn more about how Google uses data at
    <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites</a>,
    and residents of the EEA, UK, and Switzerland can review Google's
    additional consent-based controls there as well. Alternatively, you can
    opt out of some third-party vendors' use of cookies for personalized
    advertising by visiting
    <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.aboutads.info/choices</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We may use a privacy-conscious analytics tool (such as Google Analytics)
    to understand aggregate traffic patterns — for example, which calculators
    are used most, and which pages need improvement. Analytics data is
    reported in aggregate and is not linked to the numbers you enter into a
    calculator, because that data never leaves your browser in the first
    place.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies used on this site fall into two categories: cookies we set
    ourselves for basic site functionality (such as remembering your language
    preference), and cookies set by third-party services like Google AdSense
    and analytics providers as described above. Most browsers let you block or
    delete cookies through their settings; doing so may affect ad
    personalization but will not affect the calculators, since they do not
    depend on cookies to function.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    WorthCalc is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly
    collect personal information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time, for example when a
    new calculator is added or when our advertising setup changes. The
    "updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy can be sent to
    <a href="mailto:hello@example.com">hello@example.com</a>.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
